<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Inter-Arab Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Arab League Urges UN To Halt Bosnia `Massacres' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0602162394 Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network in 
Arabic 1500 GMT 6 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0602162394 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Arab League has asked the international 
community and the United Nations for immediate action to halt 
massacres of Muslims in Bosnia-Herzegovina perpetrated by the 
Serbs, who take advantage of the world silence and the blockade 
that prevents any defensive weapons from reaching the Muslims 
there. 
  In a statement made today, the Arab League General 
Secretariat called on the Security Council to use all possible 
means to restore peace to this republic according to the 
principles of law and justice and not the policy of aggression 
and occupation. 
  In its statement, the Arab League General Secretariat 
emphasized that it is following with extreme concern the tragic 
developments in Bosnia and the Serb forces' continued killing of 
unarmed civilians, especially the tragic incident that led to 
the killing and wounding of 263 Muslims when Serbs shelled the 
capital of Sarajevo yesterday. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

