<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Inter-Arab Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Arab League Chief Comments on Talks in Germany </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0502093594 Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network in 
Arabic 0500 GMT 5 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0502093594 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Arab League Secretary General Dr. 'Ismat 
'Abd-al-Majid has ended a several-day visit to Germany, during 
which he held talks with German Foreign Minister Klaus Kinkel 
and other senior German officials. 
  'Abd-al-Majid held a news conference at the end of his visit 
to Bonn last night. He said he and German officials discussed 
ways to promote Arab-European cooperation, especially with 
Germany, and efforts to resolve the Middle East problem. He 
added that the talks also dealt with Arab viewpoints on various 
issues, the Arab-European dialogue, and expansion of the 
Security Council's permanent membership. He said that he and 
the German foreign minister discussed the Bosnia-Herzegovina 
issue and the international community's stand on it, with which 
the Arab League is not satisfied. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

