<H3> <TI>   AMU Foreign Ministers Conclude Two-Day Meeting </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0402142694 Tunis Tunisian Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1300 4 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0402142694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tunis Tunisian Republic Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] The proceedings of the two-day 14th session of 
the Arab Maghreb Union [AMU] foreign ministers' council ended 
this morning. [passage omitted] 
  AMU Secretary General Mohamed Amamou gave us the following 
statement at the end of this session: 
  [Begin Amamou recording] Every presidency period is a stage 
in the joint Maghreban action. There is great hope that the 
stages of Arab Maghreb action will continue in a way that will 
be in compliance with the aspirations of peoples and work for 
the resolutions of the presidency council in the various fields 
in which they have adopted resolutions or future resolutions 
which they can adopt. Thus, our Maghreban action is always 
characterized by optimism. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

