<F P=101> Inter-Arab Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Secretariat General Issues Communique </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0402185994 Tunis Tunisian Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1700 GMT 4 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0402185994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tunis Tunisian Republic Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Arab Maghreb Union [AMU] Secretariat General has 
issued the following communique: 
  The council of foreign ministers of the member-states of AMU 
at its 14th session, held in Tunis on 3-4 February 1994, looked 
into the request of some member-states for the postponement of 
the convening of the sixth session of the presidential council 
of the union, which was scheduled for this week. Agreement was 
reached among the member-states of the union that the sixth 
session of the presidential council will be held in Tunis at a 
future date to be fixed through consultation between His 
Excellency President Zine El Abidine Ben Ali and his brothers 
the leaders of the member-states of the union. 

</TEXT>

