<F P=101> Algeria </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Confirms FIS Contacts; Official Killed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0502151794 Paris France-Info Radio in French 1430 GMT 5 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0502151794 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris France-Info Radio </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In Algeria, the authorities have confirmed that 
there have been contacts with leading representatives from the 
Islamic Salvation Front [FIS]. The two Islamist leaders, Abassi 
Madani and Ali Belhadj are reported to have approved these 
high-level contacts. 
  Nevertheless, the violence continues in Algeria. The 
subprefect of Ouled Mimoun, south of Sidi Bel Abbes, was 
murdered on Wednesday [2 February]. He was murdered by unknown 
assailants as he went to work. 

</TEXT>

