<F P=100> India </F>
<H3> <TI>   Anti-Pakistan Demonstrations Held in Kashmir </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0502133494 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 1230 
GMT 5 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0502133494 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Massive anti-Pakistan demonstrations were held in 
many parts of Jammu and Kashmir today. Several thousand people, 
mostly youths, participated in the demonstrations to protest 
against the Pakistani role in abetting and sponsoring terrorism 
in various parts of India, especially Jammu and Kashmir. 
Effigies of Pakistan Prime Minister Ms. Benazir Bhutto and 
former premier Nawaz Sharif were burned at many places by the 
activists of the Youth Congress-I and other groups. Several 
youth organizations, including the Jammu and Kashmir Pradesh 
[state] Youth Congress-I, Democratic Youth Federation of India, 
Yuva Janata Dal [Youth Wing of Janata Dal], and Youth Kashmir 
Pundit Migrants organized protest rallies before the office of 
the United National Observers Group in Jammu. Later, they 
submitted a memorandum to the group, demanding that Pakistan be 
declared a terrorist country. 
  Thousands of youths gathered at the Wagah border to protest 
against the conspiracy by Pakistan against India. Addressing 
the demonstrators, the Youth Congress-I president, Mr. Maninder 
Singh Bitta, asked Pakistan to stop encouraging terrorism in 
India and work sincerely for peace between the two countries. 

</TEXT>

