<H3> <TI>   Talks With China on Confidence-Building Measures End </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0502103894 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 0245 
GMT 5 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0502103894 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The India-China expert group has agreed on several 
issues, including its mandate and the methodology to be followed 
in its future meetings. During its two-day meeting in New 
Delhi, the group expressed satisfaction at the confidence 
building measures which are already in place. Matters relating 
to clarification of the line of actual control, reduction of 
armed forces along the line, and prior information about 
military exercises and prevention of air intrusion came up for 
discussion during the talks. The Indian side, led by Mr. Shiva 
Shankara Menon, joint secretary in the External Affairs 
Ministry, included representatives from the Defense and Home 
Ministries and the Survey of India. The Chinese delegation was 
headed by Mr. Fu Xuejhang. 

