<H3> <TI>   King: Differences Delay Yemeni Accord Signing </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN0402193294 Paris Radio Monte Carlo in Arabic 1900 GMT 4 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0402193294 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris Radio Monte Carlo </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] King Husayn has said the signing of the Yemeni 
accord, which was supposed to take place in Amman on Sunday [6 
February], has been postponed due to differences between the 
northerners and the southerners. King Husayn reiterated that 
Jordan will continue to exert efforts to resolve the Yemeni 
crisis. However, he added, some time is needed before reaching 
results. 

</TEXT>

