<H3> <TI>   Omani Minister Conveys Message to King, Departs </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN0302193394 Amman Jordan Television Network in Arabic 1800 
GMT 3 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0302193394 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman Jordan Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by political affairs reporter Salim 'Ali Dhiyab] </F>
  [Text] His Highness Crown Prince Hasan, the regent, has 
received Mr. Yusuf Bin-'Alawi Bin-'Abdallah, the minister of 
state for foreign affairs in Oman. He conveyed a verbal message 
from His Majesty Sultan Qabus Bin-Sa'id to his brother His 
Majesty King Husayn, dealing with matters of shared interest and 
Arab and world issues of mutual concern to the two brotherly 
countries. 
  Mr. Bin-'Alawi had this to say to Jordan television about 
the 
message and Oman's role in Arab fence-mending: 
  [Begin Bin-'Alawi recording] I communciated to His Highness 
Prince Hasan a message from his majesty the sultan to his 
brother his majesty the king. The message is a link in the 
chain of consultations that have marked the personal 
relationship between their majesties on matters related to joint 
Arab action, Arab solidarity, and other issues. Just like 
Jordan, the Sultanate of Oman wants to promote inter-Arab 
reconcilation. We hope both their majesties' efforts will yield 
results in order to advance the interests of the Arab nation. 
[end recording] 
  The Omani minister left Amman this afternoon concluding a 
visit to Jordan lasting several days. 
  On hand to receive and bid farewell to the minister were 
Talal Sat'an al-Hasan, the minister of state for foreign 
affairs; the director general and the chief of protocal at the 
Foreign Ministry; and the Omani ambassador in Amman. 

</TEXT>

