<F P=100> JORDAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Investigation Continues in Recent Cinema Bombings </TI></H3>
<H4>   Two Confess to Theater Blasts </H4>
<F P=102> JN0602134094 Amman Radio Jordan Network in Arabic 1200 GMT 6 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0602134094 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman Radio Jordan Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Interior Minister Salamah Hammad has stated that the 
criminals who planted explosives at the Cinema Rivoli in Amman, 
Cinema Salwa in al-Zarqa', and the al-'Akrush Supermarket in the 
town of Safut have been apprehended. The explosive charge 
planted in Safut was discovered and defused, he noted. 
  In a statement to the Jordanian News Agency, PETRA, the 
interior minister added: Muhammad 'Ali Shihadah, alias 
Abu-'Abbad, a construction worker aged 26 years, and 'Id Salih 
al-Jahalin, a plumber aged 31 years, have admitted that they 
committed these crimes. They are part of a group that will be 
uncovered later. 
  Hammad went on to say that the apprehension of these two 
criminals was the result of remarkable and persistent efforts by 
the Public Security organs since these crimes occurred. He said 
that investigations are continuing to unearth the details of 
plans to undermine the homeland's security and stability. 
  Hammad said that these two criminals who perpetrated these 
crimes, which aimed to undermine the citizens' security, have 
connections with some persons who have returned from Afghanistan. 
  Concluding his statement, Hammad said: We take pride in our 
inspired leadership, which has always rendered us loyal soldiers 
of the homeland, eager to perform our duties. We pledge to this 
leadership to remain, as King Husayn has always known us, people 
who have faith in the message, and who will keep the trust. 

</TEXT>

