Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Kuwait, 5 Feb (KUNA) -- The State Security Court 
resumed here today hearings in the case of the terrorist 
network, which attempted to assassinate former U.S. President 
George Bush during his visit to Kuwait last year, instigated and 
planned by the Iraqi intelligence. 
  On 25 December 1993, the court postponed issuing sentences 
in 
this case in which 11 Iraqi and three Kuwaiti defendants are 
involved and decided to retry the case and hear the key witness 
in this case. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

