<H3> <TI>   Planning Minister: Accord in `Precarious Situation' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN0302172594 Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network in 
Arabic 1615 GMT 3 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0302172594 </F>
<F P=104>  Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Sanaa--Yemeni Planning Minister 'Abd-al-Karim 
al-Iryani today declared that the national accord that has been 
reached to end the political crisis in Yemen is in a precarious 
situation. In a news conference, al-Iryani ruled out the 
possibility of signing that accord in Jordan next week. 
Al-Iryani said that no agreement has been reached on the 
arrangements for the signing of the accord, in Jordan or in 
Yemen. He said that this is because there are conditions that 
have been set by the Yemeni Socialist Party. 

</TEXT>

