<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Sanaa Officials Seize Plane Carrying Military Cargo </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN0602130494 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1200 GMT 6 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0602130494 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] An Interior Ministry responsible source has informed 
the Yemeni News Agency, SABA', that a Boeing 707 cargo plane 
bearing the Ugandan flag was siezed at al-Hudaydah Airport 
today, Sunday. The plane was flying from London via Athens to 
Aden, carrying a large cargo of batteries specially for military 
equipment and radio systems, which were being brought into the 
country illegally and without the knowledge or approval of the 
specialized authorities. 
  Competent authorities are carrying out investigations to 
determine the circumstances involving the arrival of this cargo 
into the country as well as those behind it. 

</TEXT>

