<F P=100> Pakistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Protests India's Sharma's Remarks on Bhutto </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0502103094 Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network in Urdu 0200 
GMT 5 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0502103094 </F>
<F P=104>  Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Urdu </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pakistan has lodged a strong protest over Indian 
President Shankar Dayal Sharma's remarks against the person of 
its prime minister. Indian High Commissioner S.K. Lambha was 
summoned to the foreign office in Islamabad yesterday and was 
told that the assault on the person of the prime minister is not 
only unjustifiable but is also against the civilized norms of 
behavior between sovereign nations. The Pakistani foreign 
office has also said that the campaign launched by India to 
malign the Pakistani prime minister cannot misguide world public 
opinion, which has openely held India responsible for the human 
rights violations in occupied Kashmir. The government of 
Pakistan very much regrets that the Indian president also has 
involved himself in the campaign. 

</TEXT>

