<F P=100> Pakistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Bhutto Reaffirms Support for `Usurped Rights' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0602150694 Islamabad PTV Television Network in English 
1400 GMT 6 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0602150694 </F>
<F P=104>  Islamabad PTV Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] The prime minister, Ms. Benazir Bhutto, has 
declared that Pakistan would not be cowed down by any threat and 
no power can restrain us from supporting the cause of 
righteousness, justice, and equality. Addressing the 
Balochistan local bodies convention in Sibi today, she said we 
have been raising our voice against injustices and atrocities 
wherever they have been committed -- be it Bosnia, Kashmir, or 
Palestine. We would continue our support for the usurped rights 
of the people and no threat can intimidate us. 
  The prime minister said we supported the brotherly people of 
Afghanistan against Soviet aggression and are making every 
effort for peace to prevail in that country so that it rebuilds 
itself with the cooperation of brotherly countries. Ms. Benazir 
Bhutto said we love Pakistan, we love the land which we achieved 
after great sacrifices and would build this country into a 
strong and prosperous state. Millions of people of the 
subcontinent rendered tremendous sacrifices and laid down their 
lives to achieve a separate homeland for Muslims of South Asia 
where they could lead a life of respect, honor and independence. 
She said democracy has been restored in Pakistan through fair 
and impartial elections and an Awami [popular] government has 
taken over the reigns of the country. This government with the 
active support of the people would make every endeavor to 
accelerate the pace of development and bring about all-round 
progress and prosperity. 
  Ms. Benazir Bhutto said it is our collective responsibility 
to work for the solidarity, integrity, and prosperity of the 
country and we must translate the dreams of the Quaed-i-Azam 
[great leader Jinnah] into reality. The people are the real 
heirs and owners of the country, and therefore, the government 
is paying due attention toward their betterment, she said. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

