<H3> <TI>   Al-Hirawi Leaves for Ivory Coast President's Funeral </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0602094394 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 0900 GMT 6 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0602094394 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Radio Lebanon </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] President Ilyas al-Hirawi left Beirut for the 
Ivory Coast at 0930 today to attend the funeral of the late 
Ivory Coast president, Felix Houphouet-Boigny. The president is 
accompanied by Ministers Faris Buwayz, Anwar al-Khalil, Muhammad 
Bassam Murtada, and deputies Ahmad 'Ajami and Ghassan Matar. He 
is also accompanied by a delegation of media representatives and 
a number of officers. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

