<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Sarid Denies Allegations of Rabin-Peres Discord </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA0502100294 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0900 GMT 5 Feb 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0502100294 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Minister Yosi Sarid, a member of the Israeli team 
negotiating with the PLO, said that it was the Palestinian 
delegation's constant vacillation which precluded the reaching 
of an agreement in Davos, and not disagreements between Prime 
Minister Rabin and Foreign Minister Peres. 
  Our political correspondent Shlomo Raz reports that Sarid 
denied allegations made by Nabil Sha'th, according to which 
inflexible instructions from Rabin foiled agreement. Sarid 
asserted that Sha'th had approved a document formulated by the 
delegations and only retracted his agreement after 'Arafat 
expressed dissatisfaction with the paper. Minister Sarid that 
an exchange of accusations between the two delegations would 
neither help nor promote the negotiations. Instead of 
continuing to analyze what happened in Davos, Sarid said, we 
must prepare for the meeting in Cairo in order to guarantee its 
success. 

</TEXT>

