<H3> <TI>   Fatah Hawks Said Disobeying PLO-Tunis </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA0602140594 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1300 GMT 6 Feb 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0602140594 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In today's cabinet session, security sources 
reported that the Fatah Hawks do not accept the authority of 
PLO-Tunis, and that since the signing of the Israel-PLO 
Declaration of Principles they have not ceased their terror 
activity. 
  Our political correspondent Shlomo Raz reports that Prime 
Minister Rabin emphasized to the ministers that in the talks 
which preceded the formulation of the Declaration of Principles 
he prevented the IDF's [Israel Defense Forces] involvement 
because at that time political decisions were being made. Now, 
however, the military echelon is involved in the negotiations 
because military decisions are being made on issues such as 
external security, safeguarding the traffic axes, and securing 
the settlements. 
  Mr. Rabin explained that he wants the 'Arafat-Peres meeting 
to proceed as planned in Cairo tomorrow. Prime Minister Rabin 
and Foreign Minister Peres will hold a private meeting this 
afternoon in order to decide on this issue. 

</TEXT>

