<H3> <TI>   Two Palestinians Killed in Clashes With IDF </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA0502124294 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1200 GMT 5 Feb 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0502124294 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A 12-year-old boy, 'Ayman al-Suri, was killed this 
afternoon in the Jabalyah refugee camp when IDF [Israel Defense 
Forces] soldiers fired at stone throwers. Our correspondent 
Moti Amir reports that this morning, two firebombs were hurled 
at IDF troops in Jabalyah and in Gaza city. There were no 
casualties and no damage was caused. A general strike was 
observed for the third consecutive day in the Gaza Strip today, 
in mourning for the death of the leader of the Fatah Hawks cell 
in Rafah, who was killed in a shootout with IDF soldiers. 
  Khayr Yusuf 'Abdallah, from the village of Bal'a in Samaria, 
was killed this morning by IDF gunfire when he attempted to flee 
his village, which was under curfew, in a car. The curfew was 
imposed in an attempt to locate stolen cars. 
  A youth was injured by soldiers' gunfire near al-Duhayshah 
refugee camp after breaking through an Army roadblock in his car. 

</TEXT>

