<H3> <TI>   Wrapup of Talks Between 'Aziz, UN Commission's Ekeus </TI></H3>
<H4>   Talks End </H4>
<F P=102> JN0502213694 Baghdad INA in Arabic 2018 GMT 5 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN0502213694 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad INA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Baghdad, 5 Feb (INA)--Iraq and the UN Special 
Commission concluded talks at the Foreign Ministry this evening. 
  Deputy Prime Minister Tariq 'Aziz headed the Iraqi 
delegation, and Foreign Minister Muhammad Sa'id al-Sahhaf 
attended. The UN delegation was headed by its Special 
Commission Chairman Rolf Ekeus. 
  During the final session, the Iraqi delegation consisted of 
Lieutenant General 'Amir Muhammad Rashid, head of the Military 
Industrialization Organization; Dr. Riyad al-Qaysi, Foreign 
Ministry under secretary; and several specialists. 
  The UN Special Commission comprised John Scott, the 
Commission's legal adviser, and Tim Tereven [name as received], 
official spokesman for the Commission. 

</TEXT>

