<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   Wrapup of Talks Between 'Aziz, UN Commission's Ekeus </TI></H3>
<H4>   Joint News Conference Held </H4>
<F P=102> JN0602101694 Baghdad INA in Arabic 0915 GMT 6 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN0602101694 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad INA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Baghdad, 6 Feb (INA)--Rolf Ekeus, chairman of the UN 
Special Commission, has described as positive his talks in 
Baghdad, which he concluded yesterday. 
  In a joint news conference with Riyad al-Qaysi, under 
secretary of the Foreign Ministry, here today, Ekeus said that 
the results of these talks have augmented the progress that the 
two sides have made during the past months. 
  Ekeus stressed that these talks have bolstered the mutual 
trust between Iraq and the UN Special Commission, thus providing 
a better atmosphere for both sides to implement relevant UN 
resolutions and for lifting the embargo on Iraqi exports. 
  He said that the two sides have agreed that the Commission 
and the International Atomic Energy Agency will submit as soon 
as possible their report to the UN Security Council on Iraq's 
adoption of the required measures in accordance with Paragraph 
22 of UN Security Council Resolution 687. 
  He stressed that in their talks, both sides dealt with 
political as well as technical issues related to the UN 
resolutions. 
  For his part, Dr. Riyad al-Qaysi stressed that progress has 
been made toward the continuation of the two sides' early 
implementation of Paragraph 22 of Resolution 687. 
  He added: From our point of view, Iraq has implemented all 
the measures pertaining to that paragraph. 
  Dr. al-Qaysi indicated that both sides have agreed to 
continue cooperation, aiming for a speedy implementation of 
Paragraph 22 of the aforementioned resolution. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

