<H3> <TI>   Arab League Informed of 27-31 Jan Airspace Violations </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN0602171694 Baghdad Republic of Iraq Radio Network in 
Arabic 1130 GMT 6 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0602171694 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad Republic of Iraq Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Iraq has informed the Arab League that the rulers of 
Saudi Arabia and Kuwait continue to provide facilities for the 
U.S., British, and French aircraft that violate the Iraqi 
airspace, thus seriously threatening Iraq's security, 
sovereignty, and national unity. 
  In a letter of protest to the Arab League secretary general 
yesterday, the Iraqi permanent representative to the Arab League 
said that from 27-31 January U.S., British, and French aircraft 
carried out 192 hostile air sorties after flying from their 
bases in Kuwait and Saudi Arabia. 
  Attaching his letter to a list detailing these violations, 
the Iraqi representative asked that it be distributed among the 
Arab member states. 

</TEXT>

