<H3> <TI>   U.S. Navy's `Illegal' Gulf Activities Protested </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0402183194 Tehran IRNA in English 1632 GMT 4 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0402183194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] United Nations Hq. (New York), Feb. 4, IRNA -- 
Iran's permanent envoy to the United Nations, Kamal Kharrazi, in 
a letter to UN Secretary General Butrus Butrus-Ghali on Thursday 
[3 February] protested the illegal activities of the U.S. Navy 
in the Persian Gulf and the Gulf of Oman. 
  Kharrazi complained that between June 25 to September 16, 
1993, the U.S. naval forces disrupted the routine patrolling of 
an Iranian air fighter and six helicopters over Iranian waters 
and threatened them to change their course. 
  In his letter Kharrazi emphasised that the Iranian interest 
section in Washington last month asked the Embassy of Pakistan 
to inform American secretary of state over the incident and to 
ask for an explanation. 
  The letter describing details of the incident was 
distributed 
as a United Nations Security Council document at the UN 
headquarters here on Thursday. 

</TEXT>

