<H3> <TI>   Besharati Appointed Head of Law Enforcement Forces </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0502115794 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 1030 GMT 5 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0502115794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Persian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] His Eminence Ayatollah Khamene'i, the eminent leader 
of the Islamic revolution and the commander in chief of the 
Armed Forces, has issued an edict appointing Interior Minister 
'Ali Mohammed Besharati as the commander in chief's deputy in 
charge of the Law Enforcement Forces of the Islamic Republic of 
Iran for a period of three years. 
  Here follows the text of the message from the eminent 
leader: 
  In the name of God, the merciful, the compassionate. 
  Your Excellency 'Ali Mohammed Besharati, the esteemed 
interior minister. Taking into consideration your revolutionary 
background, commitment, trustworthiness and caring efforts 
toward your duties, and to give greater operational power to the 
interior minister in establishing security and welfare for the 
people, I appoint you as the commander in chief's deputy in 
charge of the Law Enforcement Forces of the Islamic Republic of 
Iran for a period of three years. 
  I hope that you succeed in carrying out your 
responsibilities 
through the extensive authority entrusted to you, and the 
interest and support of the Forces' commanders and its dynamic 
personnel. 
  [Signed] Seyyed 'Ali Khamene'i 

</TEXT>

