<F P=100> LEBANON </F>
<H3> <TI>   Roundup of 4-7 Feb Clashes in Southern Region </TI></H3>
<H4>   Three SLA Soldiers Wounded </H4>
<F P=102> NC0502083194 Kafr Killa Voice of the South in Arabic 0800 
GMT 5 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0502083194 </F>
<F P=104>  Kafr Killa Voice of the South </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Three South Lebanese Army [SLA] soldiers were 
slightly injured when a mine exploded on the road between the 
villages of Markaba and Tallusah yesterday afternoon. 
  Another SLA force detonated a land mine which it had 
discovered in the Jazzin area yesterday morning. The SLA force 
suffered no casualties. 
  In the Western sector, an Israeli Army patrol came under 
terrorist fire. The patrol returned the fire. The patrol 
suffered no casualties. 

</TEXT>

