<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Arab-Israeli Talks </F>
<H3> <TI>   'Arafat, Peres, Musa Meet To Overcome `Obstacles' </TI></H3>
<H4>   Negotiations Continue in Cairo </H4>
<F P=102> NC0802114894 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1115 GMT 8 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0802114894 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 8 Feb (MENA)--Israeli Foreign Minister 
Shim'on Peres, who is visiting Cairo, has stated that 
negotiations with the Palestinian delegation will continue in 
Cairo today and tomorrow if necessary. 
  Israeli Environment Minister Yosi Sarid said the Palestinian 
and Israeli negotiators have faced no obstacles requiring 
consultation with their superiors. 
  Talks resumed this morning between the Palestinian 
delegation 
led by Ahmad Quray', alias Abu-'Ala', and the Israeli delegation 
led by Uri Savir, director general of the Israeli Foreign 
Ministry. The talks started yesterday evening and continued 
into the night. 
  A meeting is expected later today among Foreign Minister 
'Amr 
Musa, Shim'on Peres, and Yasir 'Arafat. 
  Elsewhere, Shim'on Peres and Yosi Sarid visited Filastin 
Hospital in Cairo, where an international conference is being 
held on psychiatric treatment for patients in the occupied 
territories. 

</TEXT>

