<F P=101> Algeria </F>
<H3> <TI>   Political Parties Form New Body </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0702230794 Algiers Radio Algiers Network in Arabic 2100 
GMT 7 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0702230794 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers Radio Algiers Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Three political formations, i.e. the National Party 
for Solidarity and Development [al-Hizb al-Watani lil-Tadamun wa 
al- Tanmiyah], the Boumedienist Islamic National Front 
[al-Jabhah al-- Wataniyah al-Islamiyah al-Boumedianiyah] and the 
Front of the Generations of Independence [Jabhatu Ajyal 
al-Istiqlal] announced, in a statement released today, the 
formation of the Constitutional National Movement [al-Harakah 
al-Wataniyah al-Dusturiyah]. 
  According to the statement, the formation of the movement 
comes after the dissolution of the Constitutional National Rally 
which included 12 political formations. 

</TEXT>

