<F P=100> Sudan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Condemns Mortar Attack on Sarajevo Market </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AB0802134894 Dakar PANA in English 1308 GMT 8 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AB0802134894 </F>
<F P=104>  Dakar PANA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Khartoum, 8 Feb (SUNA/PANA) -- Sudan has condemned 
Sunday's mortar attack on an outdoor market in Sarajevo in which 
68 died and another 200 were injured. The Foreign Ministry 
denounced what it said Monday was the "negative stance of the UN 
Security Council vis-a-vis these inhuman killings." It called 
for an end to what it termed was a "human rights violation in 
Bosnia- Herzegovina". The government called for the lifting of 
the arms embargo imposed on Muslims in the besieged city. The 
United Nations have been unable to determine who fired the 
single mortar round Sunday. 

</TEXT>

