<F P=100> Sudan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Various Sectors React to Attack on Mosque </TI></H3>
<H4>   Opposition Blames Regime </H4>
<F P=102> NC0602165894 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1430 GMT 6 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0602165894 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 6 Feb (MENA)--The opposition Sudanese 
National Unionist Party strongly condemned Friday's massacre at 
the Ansar al-Sunnah Mosque and said that it was one of the 
ugliest crimes perpetrated against Muslims in Sudan. 
  In a statement it issued today, the party, which is closely 
monitoring the painful events in Sudan, stressed to the whole 
world that the Islamic Front's government is ultimately 
responsible for what happened in the mosque and that the 
government's claims that foreign elements were responsible for 
the incident do not absolve it from this responsibility. 
  The statement added: Even if this accusation is true, who 
opened the country for extremists, fanatics, and terrorists from 
every corner to come and spread corruption, anxiety, and threats 
in the country and the region? 
  The statement appealed to the international community and 
world conscience to exert pressure on the Khartoum regime to 
stop its evil actions against innocent citizens and called for 
an immediate and urgent investigation. It also demanded 
punishment for the responsible criminals and killers who can 
only be the extremist groups that have been massed in the 
country. 

</TEXT>

