<H3> <TI>   UN `Neutrality,' World View of Bosnia Examined </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0802071294 Cairo MENA in Arabic 0610 GMT 8 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0802071294 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 8 Feb (MENA)--AL-AKHBAR denounces the stance 
UN officials have assumed on the massacre committed lately by 
the Serbian slaughterers besieging Sarajevo, the massacre that 
killed 68 and wounded hundreds of Muslims. 
  In an editorial today, the paper says the stance adopted by 
the UN officials since the crisis began has been one designed to 
demonstrate neutrality and ignore responsibility to preserve 
peace and stability in member states. 
  The newspaper adds that the international organization has 
left the Bosnian people easy prey for extremist ethnic gangs, 
which get the most modern weapons anywhere, while it has barred 
the victimized people's access to weapons to defend themselves. 
  The paper describes the world's position on the massacre as 
"loose and feeble," although the world claims it has reached the 
peak of civilization. 

</TEXT>

