<H3> <TI>   Vice President Receives Jordanian Delegation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN0702211794 Baghdad Republic of Iraq Radio Network in 
Arabic 1900 GMT 7 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0702211794 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad Republic of Iraq Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Taha Yasin Ramadan, Revolution Command Council 
member and vice president, has said that the rancorous enemies 
who are wagering on a war of attrition by perpetuating the 
blockade will lose their wager, just as they lost their wager on 
the war they perpetuated between Iraq and Iran for eight years. 
The Iraqis under leader President Saddam Husayn crowned this 
war with a great victory and emerged from it stronger and more 
capable, he added. 
  During a meeting today with a delegation from the Jordanian 
Arab Democratic Party, led by Samir Habashinah, the party's 
deputy secretary general and member of the Jordanian House of 
Representatives, Ramadan said that the Iraqis will foil the war 
of blockade and will emerge stronger. He pointed to what the 
Iraqis have achieved in terms of marvelous and great victories 
in their counterattack, represented by reconstructing what the 
aggressors demolished and by foiling the aggressors' schemes 
designed to deprive Iraq of both its livelihood and its elements 
of strength, progress, and reconstruction. 
  Habashinah saluted the heroic stand of President Saddam 
Husayn and the great Iraqi people. He also lauded their 
confrontation of the largest aggression against the Arab nation. 
  Habashinah stressed that the Iraqis' firmness and adherence 
to their principles and sovereignty are additional strength for 
all the Arabs, who are struggling for their nation and its 
sovereignty and progress. 
  The meeting was attended by the head of the Foreign 
Relations 
Office of the Arab Socialist Ba'th Party and Sa'd Qasim Hammudi, 
secretary general of the Arab Popular Forces Conference. 

</TEXT>

