<H3> <TI>   T-72 Tanks Reportedly Deployed in Central Iraq </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0702190894 (Clandestine) Voice of Iraqi Islamic Revolution 
in Arabic 1430 GMT 7 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0702190894 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Voice of Iraqi Islamic Revolution 
in Arabic 1430 GMT 7 Feb 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Our sources in Iraq have monitored extensive 
movements for tyrant Saddam's forces on the road linking the 
Governorates of al-Najaf and Karbala' in central Iraq. Our 
sources said in an urgent dispatch received today that dozens of 
armored military units and tank battalions were seen taking up 
positions along the road. Most of the tanks deployed by the 
regime, our sources added, are sophisticated Russian-made T-72's 
used by the Republican Guards. 
  Our sources cited well-informed sources that the deployment 
came after antiregime popular moves in central Iraq, especially 
in the Governorates of Karbala', al-Najaf, and al-Hillah. The 
sources said the command of the deployed force was instructed to 
hold military exercises and training for occupying imaginary 
targets inside cities. 
  It should be noted that the Governorates of al-Najaf and 
Karbala' were in the past few weeks the scene of heroic 
operations carried out by the Islamic resistance forces. The 
regime's centers, headquarters, and its security and party 
services were attacked, and leaflets urging citizens to rebel 
against and overthrow tyrant Saddam's regime were distributed. 

</TEXT>

