<H3> <TI>   Clashes With Money Changers Reported </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0702190794 (Clandestine) Voice of Iraqi Islamic Revolution 
in Arabic 1430 GMT 7 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0702190794 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Voice of Iraqi Islamic Revolution 
in Arabic 1430 GMT 7 Feb 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] More than 20 people were killed and scores others 
wounded in violent clashes between groups of money changers and 
special forces affiliated with tyrant Saddam's son 'Udayy in the 
money changers' market near Baghdad International Fair in 
al-Mansur suburb of Baghdad. This was reported by arrivals from 
Baghdad in Iraqi Kurdistan in the past two days. They said the 
clashes took place when the money changers refused to observe 
the regime's recent instructions banning individuals from 
dealing in currency in the Baghdad money market and restricting 
this activity to a group of brokers working directly on behalf 
of 'Udayy. 

</TEXT>

