<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Leaders React to Hizballah Attack on IDF Troops </TI></H3>
<H4>   `Sources' on Syria Using Hizballah </H4>
<F P=102> TA0802060294 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0505 GMT 8 Feb 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0802060294 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by army affairs correspondent Karmela Menashe] </F>
  [Excerpt] [passage omitted] IDF [Israel Defense Forces] 
troops on the northern border and in the security zone have been 
placed on alert, and Israel is closely following what is 
happening in the north. 
  Military and political sources say that a trend of 
escalating 
terror attacks has persisted since the beginning of the dialogue 
with the PLO. In 1993, the number of terror attacks in Lebanon 
doubled, the number of infiltration attempts increased 
considerably, and the organizations opposed to the peace process 
have exhibited a higher motivation to infiltrate into Israel and 
carry out attacks. The sources say Syria will continue to use 
Hizballah, as it has in previous years, according to its 
political needs. 

</TEXT>

