<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Beilin: Government To Resign If Defeated in Referendum </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA0802063294 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0505 GMT 8 Feb 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0802063294 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Addressing a meeting of the World Jewish Congress 
in Washington yesterday, Deputy Foreign Minister Yosi Beilin 
said that if the government is defeated in the referendum on 
peace with Syria, it will quit on the spot. 
  [Begin Beilin recording, in English] If the results of the 
referendum will be negative, we will resign the same day, and 
then another government which doesn't believe that it is 
possible to make peace in our generation will take the reins of 
the rule and will decide for the future of Israel. [end 
recording] 

</TEXT>

