<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Three Tzomet MK's Suspend Decision To Resign </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA0602143594 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1400 GMT 6 Feb 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0602143594 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tzomet Knesset members [MK's], Salmovitz, Goldfarb, 
and Segev have decided to suspend their decision to resign from 
Tzomet and have pulled back the letter of resignation they sent 
to the Knesset House Committee demanding to be recognized as a 
separate faction. 
  Our party affairs correspondent Shmu'el Tal reports that 
MK's 
Salmovitz, Goldfarb, and Segev are now seeking to reconvene 
Tzomet's Central Committee within two weeks in order to discuss 
their demand that their allegations of financial mismanagement 
in the movement be investigated. The MK's said that if their 
suspicions prove true, they will demand that Tzomet Director 
General Doron Shmu'eli take a leave of absence until the 
investigation into the matter is concluded. 
  MK Ester Salmovitz, who is deputy speaker of the Knesset, 
explained that she and her two colleagues would retain their 
posts until the Central Committee convened. Our correspondent 
reports that Tzomet Chairman Refa'el Eytan announced that he 
would reply to the three MK's request in several hours. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

