<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rabin, Klaus Sign Cooperation Accord </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0702222394 Prague Stanice Praha Radio Network in Czech 
2130 GMT 7 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0702222394 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague Stanice Praha Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Czech </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In Jerusalem today, Czech Prime Minister Vaclav 
Klaus and Israeli Prime Minister Yitzhaq Rabin signed a joint 
statement on the promotion of economic relations between Israel 
and the Czech Republic. According to Prime Minister Klaus, the 
document carries a decision on immediate preparation for a 
further step toward the liberalization of bilateral trade. This 
step should result in an agreement on a free-trade zone between 
the Czech Republic and Israel in the very near future. 
  At the same time, the Czech Republic and Israel have 
succeeded in concluding the two-year long discussion on the text 
of the bilateral agreement on the protection of investment and 
on profit repatriation. At a news conference, Prime Minister 
Klaus returned to the possibility of Czech arms exports to the 
so-called sensitive countries. He repeated that arms exports 
were carried out on the basis of a government license and in 
line with the law. 

</TEXT>

