<H3> <TI>   Meshkini in Qom Says Inflation Discussed With `Leader' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0402204294 Tehran IRIB Television Second Program Network 
in Persian 1532 GMT 4 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0402204294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRIB Television Second Program Network 
in Persian 1532 GMT 4 Feb 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Persian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Second Friday prayers sermon by Ayatollah Meshkini, member </F>
of the Assembly of Experts and senior lecturer at the Qom 
theological school, on 4 February -- recorded] 
  [Excerpt] [passage omitted] You should be somewhat 
patient. You should wait for a while. You have done something 
great. Your revolution is great. It has had many difficulties. 
You should know that with all these high prices and all these 
problems... [pauses] You will forgive me for taking so long to 
speak, but I am constantly unhappy about this issue, these high 
prices and problems. I should even tell you this: in the 
meeting that members of the Assembly of Experts had with the 
leader, despite the fact that it was not the place for such 
discussions and the issue did not concern the experts, it was 
put to their excellencies, the leader and the president as 
follows: Sir, you who are the first person of the country, and 
Sir, you who are the second person of the country -- both of you 
are present -- and we, members of the Assembly of Experts have a 
different task. But, we put forward this issue: the nation is 
unhappy with high prices, inflation, and some other matters. Be 
kind enough to think more of the nation. 
  This was discussed in that meeting and this is what the 
leader said in response: There has been no occasion in which I 
have gotten together with the president, two of us or more, and 
not discussed the issue of high prices, inflation, and people's 
problems. 
  You people should not worry. It is natural for such problems 
to exist. The hope is that the country's infrastructure has 
been well built, the result of which we will soon see. Be 
patient and, God willing, you shall receive both the goodness of 
the world as well as the hereafter. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

