<F P=100> SOUTH ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Azerbaijani President Meets Va'ezi in Baku </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0802083294 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 0430 GMT 8 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0802083294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Persian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Azerbaijani president met the deputy foreign 
minister for Europe and Asia in Baku and congratulated him on 
the anniversary of the victory of the Islamic revolution, 
calling for accelerating the implementation of memoranda of 
understanding between Tehran and Baku. He said that Azerbaijan 
will do its best toward this end. 
  Aliyev described President Hashemi-Rafsanjani's visit to 
Baku 
as a turning point in bilateral relations and expressed the hope 
that during his visit to Iran, new ground for expanding 
bilateral relations will be examined. 
  During the meeting, the Azerbaijani president explained the 
latest developments in the Karabakh conflict and restated his 
country's wish for a peaceful solution of the conflict, pointing 
out that the Azerbaijani forces are sufficiently ready to defend 
the Republic's territorial integrity. 
  During the meeting, Va'ezi stated that one objective of his 
visit to Azerbaijan is to follow up the process of implementing 
the bilateral memoranda of understanding. 

</TEXT>

