<H3> <TI>   Defense Ministry Denies Arms Sent Somalia's Aidid </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0702193394 Tehran IRNA in English 1811 GMT 7 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0702193394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, Feb. 7, IRNA -- The Islamic Republilc of 
Iran has never delivered any weaponry for supporters of General 
Farah Aidid of Somalia, an informed source at the Defence 
Ministry said here today. 
  The source said circulation of such unfounded news is in 
line 
with sinister plots aimed at distorting the image of the Islamic 
Republic of Iran in the world. 
  A former commander of the U.S-led multinational forces in 
Somalia had claimed last Saturday that Aidid supporters receive 
arms from Iran, Sudan and Iraq. 
  The source also denied claimes by an Arabic weekly that Iran 
held clandestine talks with the Czech Republic for the purchase 
of Russian weapons. 

</TEXT>

