<H3> <TI>   Expansion of Ties Discussed With Ukrainian Group </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0702202294 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran in 
English 1930 GMT 7 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0702202294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] At a meeting between the head of the Ukrainian 
Parliament's Foreign Policy Commission and the Islamic Republic 
of Iran's deputy foreign minister, Mr. Va'ezi, the expansion of 
bilateral relations and regional and international issues were 
discussed. In the meeting the two sides stressed that in case 
peace and stability are established in the region, the little 
countries would be able to expand cooperation in proportion to 
improvement of their situation. 
  The trip of the Iranian president and the speaker of the 
Islamic Consultative Assembly in response to visit of the 
Ukrainian president and the speaker of the parliament to Tehran 
was also reviewed in the meeting. 

