<F P=101> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Resistance Activity in Lebanon Examined </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0802072494 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 0445 GMT 8 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0802072494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Persian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Commentary prepared by the News Research and Commentaries </F>
Group] 
  [Text] The Zionist regime has admitted that the bold attack 
by Lebanon's Islamic Resistance mujahidin against Israeli 
military patrols in the occupied area in south Lebanon killed 
four Zionists and wounded two. 
  Although in such cases, the Zionist regime, which is 
helpless 
when it comes to such operations by the Muslim revolutionaries, 
always resorts to blind attacks on residential areas and finds 
many innocent Lebanese people rolling in blood, the continuation 
of the anti-Zionist resistance is of extreme political 
significance. Overtly colluding with the United States during 
the past two years, the Zionist regime has tried to make it look 
as if it seeks peace and attempted to hide its aggressive nature 
by participating in the so-called peace conference and by 
propagating false slogans. But the continuing operations by the 
Islamic Resistance mojahidin thwart much of this effort by 
Israel and clarify that the Zionist regime continues to occupy 
part of Lebanon and some other Arab countries and that it also 
extensively violates international regulations. 
  The operations by Lebanon's Muslim mujahidin against the 
Zionist occupiers also clarify another reality: Contrary to what 
the heads of some Arab states claim, Tel Aviv is vulnerable. 
Justifying their participation in the compromising talks with 
Israel in Washington, the Arab governments always speak of 
upsetting the Middle East's military balance in Israel's favor. 
But if this is true, then the operations by the Lebanese Muslim 
mujahidin show that having faith in the struggle against this 
usurping regime can alter the material and power balance to a 
large extent. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

