<H3> <TI>   `Reactionary' Deputies' Opposition to Price Hikes Noted </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0502212994 (Clandestine) Voice of Mojahed in Persian 1800 
GMT 5 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0502212994 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Voice of Mojahed </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Persian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The budget bill of the insolvent regime met with 
greater opposition this time due to the fear and apprehension of 
the reactionary Majles deputies of the explosive conditions in 
society and mounting protests by the people. 
  One of the reactionary Majles deputies, Khamushi, said that 
the 50.9 percent increase in current prices was shattering and 
stated: Unfortunately this budget will raise inflation to 50-60 
percent. 
  It is worth mentioning that in the course of the discussions 
on the regime's budget bill, 120 of the reactionary Majles 
deputies, who were terrified of the explosion of popular 
discontent against high prices, presented a triple urgency bill 
to the Majles that stipulated that the government should be 
stripped of all authority to raise prices and grant only the 
Majles this right. 

</TEXT>

