<F P=101> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Nonoil Export Figures Show Increase by Weight, Value </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0802075194 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 0430 GMT 8 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0802075194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Persian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] During the past 10 months, the country's nonoil 
exports increased 58 percent by weight and 33 percent by value 
on the same period last year. According to figures published by 
the Customs Organization, 4.642 million tonnes of nonoil goods 
worth 319 billion rials were exported during the past 10 months. 
  Hand-woven wool and silk carpets, pistachio nuts, copper, 
iron, steel, chemicals, copper and aluminum containers, hides, 
and dates were among the most important export items during this 
period. 

</TEXT>

