<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Socialists Hail Amman Decision, Deny `Conditions' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN0702212994 Baghdad INA in Arabic 2055 GMT 7 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN0702212994 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad INA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Sanaa, 7 Feb (INA)--The Yemeni Socialist Party 
[YSP], led by Vice President 'Ali Salim al-Bid, has welcomed the 
decision by the Yemeni parties dialogue committee that set the 
Jordanian capital, Amman, as the venue for signing the accord 
document in the near future. 
  In press statements tonight, Salim Salih Muhammad, member of 
the Yemeni Presidential Council and YSP assistant secretary 
general, said his party reaffirms its full support for all 
sincere efforts exerted, and resolutions taken, by the political 
parties dialogue committee to set a date for signing the 
document in the near future. Salim Salih Muhammad denied that 
his party has set any conditions or reservations that prevent 
the implementation of the committee's resolutions. 

</TEXT>

