<F P=100> JORDAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Brutal Massacre' in Sarajevo Market Denounced </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN0702132694 Amman Radio Jordan Network in Arabic 1200 GMT 7 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0702132694 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman Radio Jordan Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In a statement issued today, the House of 
Representatives has appealed to people with a live conscience, 
regardless of their positions, especially world parliaments, the 
Security Council, the United Nations, and human rights 
organizations, to work seriously to end the crimes committed by 
the Serbs against Muslims in Bosnia-Herzegovina. 
  The statement asked for severe, deterrent punitive measures 
against the aggressive Serbs and immediately lifting the siege 
of the city of Sarajevo and all other Islamic cities in 
Bosnia-Herzegovina. It also urged supplying the Bosnians with 
arms, equipment, food, and medicine, and allowing them to defend 
themselves by lifting the arms embargo, if the international 
forces do not immediately oppose the aggression against land, 
man, and human values. 
  The statement asserted that the painful, brutal massacre 
against Sarajevo by the shells of the Serbs, which killed or 
injured hundreds of people and targeted defenseless civilians -- 
elderly, women, and children -- is a link in the brutal 
aggression against innocent Muslims. The massacre took place 
amid international silence and mere verbal decisions. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

