<F P=100> LEBANON </F>
<H3> <TI>   Palestinian Reportedly Admits to Murder of Diplomat </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0702175994 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 1630 GMT 7 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0702175994 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Radio Lebanon </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] There have been important developments in the 
investigation into the assassination of Jordanian diplomat Na'ib 
al-Ma'ayitah nine days ago. 
  Security sources this afternoon confirmed a REUTER report 
that the Lebanese police have arrested a Palestinian, who 
admitted that he assassinated al-Ma'ayitah. Citing security 
sources, REUTER reported that the accused belongs to a 
Palestinian fedayeen group, and that he is currently being 
questioned. The agency added that the investigation by security 
men has led to the arrest of two people belonging to a 
Palestinian organization in connection with al-Ma'ayitah's 
assassination last Saturday. 
  When Interior Minister Bisharah Mirhij was asked about 
additional information on this matter, he replied that the case 
is in the hands of the judiciary, and that the investigation is 
continuing. 

</TEXT>

