<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Arab-Israeli Talks </F>
<H3> <TI>   Mubarak, Musa Mediate PLO-Israeli Talks in Cairo </TI></H3>
<H4>   Sha'th: `No Results' Achieved </H4>
<F P=102> NC0802152894 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1442 GMT 8 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0802152894 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 8 Feb (MENA)--Dr. Nabil Sha'th, political 
adviser to Palestinian President Yasir 'Arafat, told 
correspondents today that negotiations between the Palestinian 
and Israeli delegations have been positive so far but that no 
results have been achieved. 
  Faysal al-Husayni, official in charge of the occupied 
territories, said: We hope that matters will continue to 
proceed well but we have not finished the talks yet. 
  Uri Savir, director general of the Israeli Foreign Ministry, 
said that the clauses of the Davos document are being discussed 
one by one and it is too early to talk about results. He 
stressed that the atmosphere during the negotiations was good. 
He added that all the issues raised were discussed during the 
talks, which lasted all last night and today. 
  The members of the Israeli and Palestinian delegations made 
these statements at the end of the meeting in al-Andalus Palace, 
Heliopolis, which lasted more than seven hours, and while they 
were on their way to the working luncheon given by Foreign 
Minister 'Amr Musa at the hotel across from the palace. 

</TEXT>

