<H3> <TI>   Mubarak, Musa Mediate PLO-Israeli Talks in Cairo </TI></H3>
<H4>   Mubarak-'Arafat-Peres Meeting Ends </H4>
<F P=102> NC0802193294 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1810 GMT 8 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0802193294 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 8 Feb (MENA)--Muhammad 'Abd-al-Mun'im, head 
of the Presidential Press Office, said at the end of the session 
of talks that President Husni Mubarak held with Palestinian 
President Yasir 'Arafat and Israeli Foreign Minister Shim'on 
Peres that President 'Arafat and Peres will resume their 
meetings at the Egyptian Foreign Ministry later tonight in the 
presence of Foreign Minister 'Amr Musa. 
  He added that the talks will probably be resumed tomorrow 
morning, Wednesday. He said the Palestinian president's 
political adviser Yasir 'Abd-Rabbuh [title as received] and 
Israeli Environment Minister Yosi Sarid participated in the 
approximately one-hour tripartite Mubarak-'Arafat-Peres meeting. 

</TEXT>

