<F P=101> Arab-Israeli Talks </F>
<H3> <TI>   Mubarak, Musa Mediate PLO-Israeli Talks in Cairo </TI></H3>
<H4>   Sarid: Talks Will Take `Long Time' </H4>
<F P=102> NC0802223394 Cairo MENA in Arabic 2200 GMT 8 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0802223394 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Foreign Minister 'Amr Musa held a one-hour meeting 
with Israeli Foreign Minister Shim'on Peres tonight in an 
attempt to remove obstacles delaying the implementation of the 
Gaza-Jericho accord. 
  After the meeting, Musa, Peres, and the Israeli delegation 
members left for al-Andalus Palace to meet Palestinian President 
Yasir 'Arafat. 
  Musa and Peres refused to give any statements, but Israeli 
Environment Minister Yosi Sarid said: We are continuing the 
negotiations and I believe this will go on throughout the night. 
He noted that the talks will take a long time. 

</TEXT>

