<F P=100> Inter-Arab Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   League Chief on UNSC Seats for Arabs, Germany </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0902110394 Cairo MENA in Arabic 0920 GMT 9 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0902110394 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Cairo, 9 Feb (MENA)--Arab League Secretary 
General Dr. 'Ismat 'Abd-al-Majid has said that during his recent 
visit to Bonn he told German officials that the Arab side 
generally supports Germany's acquirement of a permanent seat at 
the UN Security Council [UNSC], but any decision in this matter 
will have to be made by the Arab League Council. 
  Dr. 'Abd-al-Majid told MENA that the United Nations should 
treat the Arab region as a geographical unit entitled to a 
permanent seat in the UNSC in the event that the latter's 
membership is expanded in accordance with the proposal made by 
UN Secretary General Butrus Butrus-Ghali. 
  Dr. 'Abd-al-Majid said that granting a permanent seat at the 
UNSC to the Arab group would help boost relations between the 
Arab World, Europe, and the rest of the World. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

