<H3> <TI>   Al-'Asifah Forces Claim Attack on Chemical Factory </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN0802194694 (Clandestine) Al-Quds Palestinian Arab Radio in 
Arabic 1730 GMT 8 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0802194694 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Al-Quds Palestinian Arab Radio </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A military spokesman for the General Command of the 
al-'Asifah Forces -- the command of the Fatah forces inside the 
occupied territories -- has stated the following: 
  Our cells operating inside the occupied homeland have 
planted 
advanced explosive charges in the Haifa chemical factory north 
of the industrial zone, which is adjacent to the Haifa oil 
refineries. 
  The charges went off at 1300 on 7 February destroying the 
factory and setting huge fires that spread to neighboring 
factories and installations. 
  The military spokesman added that, since the operation, 
rescue and fire fighting teams, the police, and the mobile 
environment protection unit for treating dangerous materials 
have been making great attempts to place the situation under 
control, while clouds of black smoke covered the whole Gulf of 
Haifa. 

</TEXT>

