<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   'Arafat Adviser Protests Murder of Hawks Leader </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA0802155094 Jerusalem AL-QUDS in Arabic 5 Feb 94 pp 1, 19 </F>
<F P=103> TA0802155094 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem AL-QUDS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By Da'ud Kuttab] </F>
  [Excerpt] Jerusalem -- Jibril al-Rajub, adviser to 
Palestinian President Yasir 'Arafat, has protested the killing 
of Salim Muwafi, the Fatah Hawks leader in Gaza, by the Israeli 
forces. He considered this act as an attempt to kill the peace 
process. 
  In an exclusive interview with AL-QUDS, al-Rajub said that 
the Palestinian leadership regards the Fatah Hawks as part of 
the forces that have to protect the national authority. 
Consequently, we have to provide security for them. 
  Regarding the peace process, al-Rajub accused Israeli Prime 
Minister Yitzhaq Rabin of responsibility for hampering the peace 
process, and said: We realize that Rabin is the key figure in 
Israel, but apparently he regrets signing the Oslo accord. 
Therefore, he is trying to hinder what was agreed on in Davos. 
  Al-Rajub said that the PLO is ready to sign the drafts that 
were agreed on in Davos. It is also ready to take over power 
within 24 hours after the Israeli withdrawal. 
  'Arafat's occupied territories' affairs adviser said that 
the 
Palestinian side considers a Palestinian-Israeli summit to be 
warranted. He also expressed his apprehension at the 
perpetuation of the current situation, which can only lead to 
frustration, opposition to the peace process, and an increase in 
the phenomena of internal and foreign violence. [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

