<H3> <TI>   Fourteen Wounded by IDF in Gaza, West Bank </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA0802200694 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1900 GMT 8 Feb 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0802200694 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Fourteen people were wounded in incidents with the 
IDF [Israel Defense Forces] in the West Bank and the Gaza Strip 
today. Our correspondent Nisim Qeynan reports that nine people 
were injured in the Jabalyah refugee camp and three in 
al-Shati'. Palestinian sources say that five of the wounded are 
children under 12. 
  Our correspondent Gil Litman reports that a youth was 
wounded 
by IDF gunfire in Janin after he threw metal bars and stones at 
soldiers. A Hebron resident was slightly injured by a petrol 
bomb which was thrown at an IDF patrol. 

</TEXT>

