<F P=100> Sudan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Denies Reports on Operations in East, West </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  EA0802192094 Khartoum SUNA in French 1631 GMT 8 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> EA0802192094 </F>
<F P=104>  Khartoum SUNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Khartoum, 8 Feb (SUNA) -- The Sudanese Government on 
8 February categorically denied the unfounded accusations 
contained in a communique issued by the U.S. State Department on 
military operations in the Eastern and Western Equatoria regions. 
  In the communique issued Tuesday in Khartoum in response to 
the U.S. accusations, the Sudanese Foreign Ministry stressed the 
United States double standards, noting that while the United 
States was referring to imaginary military operations in 
southern Sudan, it maintained total silence on Israel's deadly 
operations in the occupied territories. The communique stressed 
that the military operations in southern Sudan were nothing but 
fighting between rebel factions and that the people's armed 
forces only fired in cases of legitimate defense. 
  The communique also confirmed the commitment of the Sudanese 
Government to all the agreements on humanitarian aid, including 
those signed with the United Nations, which stipulate the 
facilitation of the transport of relief material to war victims 
in southern Sudan. 
  The United States' support for the rebel movement and for 
its 
springboard and these unfounded accusations were phenomena which 
could encourage the rebel movement to escalate the war and to 
reject all initiatives designed to achieve a peaceful solution 
to the problem in southern Sudan, the communique said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

