<F P=100> Sudan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry Statement Condemns Sarajevo Events </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  EA0802193094 Khartoum SUNA in Arabic 1430 GMT 8 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> EA0802193094 </F>
<F P=104>  Khartoum SUNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Khartoum, 8 Feb (SUNA) -- The Foreign Ministry 
yesterday issued a statement on the massacre recently 
perpetrated by the Serbs in Sarajevo, in which over 100 Bosnian 
Muslim citizens fell victim. The statement condemend the heinous 
crime and reaffirmed Sudan's (?denunciation) of the failure and 
conspiracies of the great powers. 
  The statement condemned the UN Security Council's negative 
stance towards the massacre. It expressed Sudan's concern over 
the international community's silence in response to the 
violation of human rights in Bosnia. The statement said that 
what the Serbs were doing in Bosnia was unprecedented since what 
the Nazis did during the Hitlerite era and that the UN's failure 
was exactly like the League of Nations' failure to stop the 
crimes of the Nazis, which lost it the confidence of the peoples 
of the world (?at that time). 
  The statement appealed to the peace-loving forces and all 
states to confront this inhuman (?whirlpool), to stand firmly by 
the Muslim people of Bosnia, to pressure the Security Council 
into discharging its duty to protect the Bosnian people's 
legitimate rights and lift the arms embargo imposed on the 
Bosnian people to enable them to defend themselves, strike at 
the Serbian forces to destroy their military concentrations and 
to immediately evict them from the Bosnian territories. 

</TEXT>

