<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Salih Addresses Celebration Marking Seige on Sanaa </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN0802151094 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1200 GMT 8 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0802151094 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Brother Lieutenant General 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih, 
Presidential Council chairman, accompanied by Presidential 
Council Member 'Abd-al-'Aziz 'Abd-al-Ghani and House of 
Representatives Speaker Shaykh 'Abdallah Bin-Husayn al-Ahmar, 
this morning attended the celebration organized by the Sanaa 
branch of the General People's Congress at the Cultural Center 
in Sanaa marking the 26th anniversary of the 70-day siege on 
Sanaa, December 1967 to February 1968 and the Yemeni people's 
triumph in the 70-day epic against the forces of tyranny and 
backwardness. 
  Brother Lt. Gen. 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih, Presidential Council 
chairman, delivered a speech in which he said he was happy to 
attend this celebration marking the 26th anniversary of the 
siege on valiant Sanaa and the anniversary of the 70-day 
(?immortal) epic. He said: I am very pleased to see these 
national symbols and historic leaders, who had the honor to 
defend the revolution and the republic and defeat the [word 
indistinct] savage onslaught by the antirevolution and 
antirepublic forces during the 70-day siege on valiant Sanaa. 
On behalf of the Presidential Council -- the political 
leadership of united Yemen -- we have decided to award the 
70-day Medal to the city of Sanaa and the 70-day Medal to all 
the virtuous martyrs who fell during the 70-day epic and to all 
disabled veterans. [Words indistinct] of all historic, militant 
figures and leaders, and the shaykhs, dignitaries, social 
figures, and fighters who played prominent roles during that 
immortal, heroic epic. 
  The brother chairman added: As we approach the beginning of 
the holy month of Ramadan, we had hoped that we would have been 
able to sign the accord document achieved by the Political 
Forces Dialogue Committee on this day -- the 26th anniversary of 
the defeat of the siege on valiant Sanaa, in order to rescue our 
people from this regrettable crisis, which benefits none of us. 
[Word indistinct] to those who are responsible for fabricating 
this crisis, which is hurting our people, bringing price hikes 
and destroying their stable and tranquil life. It is an 
occasion on which we renew the call to all of our citizens, 
particularly the political forces, to pool their forces to 
preserve unity and democracy and [word indistinct] the firm 
militant spirit, with which our people preserved the march of 
revolution and the republic. 

</TEXT>

