<F P=102>  NC0802201894 Beirut Voice of Lebanon in Arabic 1715 GMT 8 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0802201894 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Voice of Lebanon </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Fatah-the Revolutionary Council [FRC], led by 
Abu-Nidal, denied today that it is connected with the murder 10 
days ago of a Jordanian diplomat in Beirut. 
  In a statement released in Beirut, the movement said: We 
affirm that we have no connection, either closely or distantly, 
with the assassination of the first secretary [as heard] of the 
Jordanian Embassy in Lebanon. 
  The FRC statement asserted its confidence in the Lebanese 
judiciary and its integrity. The statement accused various 
agencies and parties of being behind this well-devised scenario, 
as the FRC statement put it. 

</TEXT>

