<F P=100> LEBANON </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Resistance' Activities in South Updated </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0802130694 (Clandestine) Radio Free Lebanon in Arabic 1145 
GMT 8 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0802130694 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Radio Free Lebanon </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] At around 1145 today, the Lebanese resistance 
shelled and launched several attacks on the Israeli positions in 
al-Ghizlan and Sujud. The Israeli forces retaliated with 
intensive artillery bombardment of several villages in Iqlim 
al-Tuffah. The clashes later developed into artillery duels 
between Tallat Sujud and the resistance positions in Iqlim 
al-Tuffah in which 155-mm and 120-mm artillery was used. 
Israeli aircraft flew intensive sorties over the central and 
western sectors and over Tyre, breaking the sound barrier more 
than once. 
  According to our correspondent in al-Biqa', a South Lebanese 
Army [SLA] foot patrol of 12, backed by a tank, crossed the 
contact line in the Zhaghlah-Hasbayya sector at 1000 today, 
advanced 2 km north of the security zone toward Mimis valley, 
and stopped 1 km from the Lebanese Army positions. The Army 
personnel in the area were placed on alert and took up combat 
positions. The SLA patrol returned to its position at 1200. 
Our correspondent said that Israeli Merkava tanks were spotted 
moving along the Kawkaba axis and fired five artillery shells at 
the al-Dallafi-Jabal al-Dahr axis. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

