<H3> <TI>   Navy Launches New Category Missile Boat </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA0802145394 Tel Aviv HA'ARETZ in Hebrew 8 Feb 94 p A4 </F>
<F P=103> TA0802145394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tel Aviv HA'ARETZ </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by military correspondent Eytan Rabin] </F>
  [Excerpt] The Israel Navy yesterday received the 
Nirit-category missile boat which will bear the name of Kidon. 
The boat's construction began at Israel Shipyards some two 
years as part of the plan to upgrade the Israel Navy missile 
warships. The boat was designed in Israel on the basis of many 
years of operational experience with missile boats. 
  The boat's body is identical to that of Saar 4.5. It is 
61.7-meter long and 7-meter wide, and its maximum displacement 
is 488 metric tons. The vessel will be equipped with 
sophisticated modern means of warfare, including an electronic 
combat system, a ship- detecting radar system, aircraft and 
missiles, a control and monitoring system, Gabriel missiles, 
Harpoon missiles, Vulcan and Phalanx antiaircraft guns, and 
Barak, the Israeli-developed antimissile missile. The vessel's 
maximum speed is 31 knots, and it will accommodate a crew of 45 
officers and soldiers. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

