<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Three `Terrorists' Given Life Sentences for Murder </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA0602084594 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0800 GMT 6 Feb 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0602084594 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] This morning, the three terrorists who murdered 
Li'or Tubul, Ronen Qaramani, Rafi Doron, and Yehoshu'a Friedberg 
were given four consecutive life sentences each. Two of them 
were given additional 20 years in prison for attempted murder. 
The Jerusalem District Court handed down the sentence after 
convicting them upon their own admission. 
  Our correspondent Mira Amsalem reports that in an 
unprecedented move, the president of the court did not allow one 
of the defendants to complete his statement before the sentence 
was issued in view of the political nature of his remarks, as 
the judge put it. After the sentencing, Qaramani's brother 
tried to attack one of the murderers, but was stopped. 

</TEXT>

