<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] The Senate today held a session under speaker 
Ahmad al-Lawzi to discuss a number of subjects on its agenda. 
  Details in the following report by Jamal al-'Abbadi: 
  [Begin al-'Abbadi recording] The Senate denounced the Serb 
aggression on the Republic of Bosnia-Herzegovina and the ongoing 
ethnic cleansing drive targeting the republic's peaceful people. 
A statement issued by the Senate today appealed to the 
international community to take military action to stop the 
aggression and lift the arms embargo on the republic to enable 
the Bosnians to defend themselves. [passage omitted] 
  Responding to a request by Senator Hammad al-Ma'ayitah, 
Deputy Prime Minister Dr. Ma'n Abu-Nuwar said investigations are 
still continuing into the martyrdom of Na'ib 'Imran 
al-Ma'ayitah, counselor at the Jordanian Embassy in Beirut, and 
the explosive devices that went off in Cinema Rivoli in Amman 
and Cinema Salwa in al-Zarqa'. The government, he said, can 
not, for the time being, go further than the facts revealed by 
the interior minister. The deputy prime minister praised the 
watchful eye of Jordan's public security agencies. [end 
recording] 

