<F P=100> JORDAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Brutal Aggression' Against Sarajevo Denounced </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN0802193494 Amman Jordan Television Network in Arabic 1800 
GMT 8 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0802193494 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman Jordan Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["Text" of statement issued by the Jordanian Government on </F>
"the savage aggression against innocent Muslims in Sarajevo;" 
date not given -- read by announcer] 
  [Text] The Jordanian Government has followed with deep 
concern the reports on the painful and bloody massacre to which 
Sarajevo, the capital of Bosnia-Herzegovina, was exposed and in 
which a large number of defenseless civilian children, women, 
and elderly people were killed. 
  As the Jordanian Government denounces the brutal aggression 
against innocent Muslims in Sarajevo and strongly condemns this 
fierce barbarism, which ignores all values, ideals, and human 
rights, it calls on the international community to move 
immediately to shoulder its responsibility to save the innocent 
Muslims in Bosnia-Herzegovina from the continuing aggression and 
to work toward ending the siege on the Bosnian capital. 
  The Jordanian Government appeals to the UN Security Council, 
the United Nations, and human rights organization to work 
earnestly to stop the bloodshed and achieve security, 
tranquility, and peace for the people of Bosnia-Herzegovina who 
are being exposed, day and night, to human rights violations 
before the eyes of the world. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

