<F P=100> JORDAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Efforts' Target Israeli Antiquities Excavations </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN0602163894 Amman AL-DUSTUR in Arabic 6 Feb 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> JN0602163894 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman AL-DUSTUR </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] AL-DUSTUR has learned from official sources that 
competent agencies have made efforts regarding the excavations 
Israel is making in search of antiquities in the border areas, 
which encroach on the antiquities of the Jordanian territories. 
  The sources said Jordanian efforts in this regard came about 
following Western news reports of Israeli excavations searching 
for antiquities in the Qumran area north of the Dead Sea. The 
Qumran area is believed to be the home of important historical 
scrolls that date back to the first century A.D. 
  The sources indicated the Qumran area is Jordanian territory 
that Israel occupied in the aftermath of the 1967 war. The 
Israeli occupation of this territory is believed to be listed on 
the agenda of the Jordanian-Israeli peace negotiations, in order 
to ensure its return to Jordanian sovereignty. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

