<H3> <TI>   Al-Asad Receives Algerian President's Envoy </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN0802185194 Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network in 
Arabic 1615 GMT 8 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0802185194 </F>
<F P=104>  Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] At 1300 today, His Excellency President Hafiz 
al-Asad received Mr. Mohamed (Saidi), chief of the Algerian 
presidential office and envoy of the president, the Algerian 
ambassador in Damascus, and the Algerian Embassy staff. (Saidi) 
gave the president a message from Algerian President Liamine 
Zeroual, in which he extends his personal and the Algerian 
people's condolences over the death of Staff Major Basil 
al-Asad. They talked about Arab and world issues, as well as 
Algerian developments. Mr. (Saidi) conveyed President Zeroual's 
appreciation for President al-Asad's efforts to advance Arab 
causes and supreme Arab interests. He expressed Algeria's 
interest in more advanced ties with Syria in all fields. His 
excellency the president thanked the Algerian president for his 
sympathies and his appreciation for Syria's pan-Arab stands. 
President al-Asad told him Syria wished to see relations with 
brotherly Algeria grow further. 

</TEXT>

